Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light buff-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Klenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0165.12.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1126)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
